# 👥 Customer Analytics & Retention Dynamics

This section evaluates the corporate consumer base, mapping client engagement frequencies, churn risk horizons, and geographic distribution profiles to preserve retention equity.

---

## 💻 Customer Analytics View

The primary interface delivers an operational audit of active customer volumes, purchasing behaviors, and geographic migration out of active cycles.
![Customer Analytics](Customer.png)

### 📈 Core Business Drivers & Operational Balance
* **Total Consumer Footprint:** The corporate ecosystem maintains **635 Total Active Customers** across all operational trading territories.
* **Transactional Value Scale:** The Average Order Value (AOV) stands exceptionally strong at **$20.78K**, driving high baseline financial scale per conversion.
* **Fulfillment Volume:** System throughput recorded **3,796 Total Orders** successfully processed through the pipeline during the active lifecycle.
* **Immediate Retention Risk:** The system flags **66 Customers with No Sales**, pinpointing an immediate pipeline leak of inactive accounts requiring tactical re-engagement.
* **Order Frequency Dynamics:** The purchasing distribution is heavily front-loaded; **235 customers** operate on a single-order baseline (4 orders tier), followed by **145 customers** at the 8-orders tier, showing a steep drop-off as order volume requirements scale up.
* **Geographic Value Alignment:** The **Southwest** region stands out as the dominant economic anchor, delivering **115 customers** and generating **$12M in Profit**, showing superior territorial conversion efficiency compared to other markets.

